                <button class="collapsible">April 20, 2020</button>
                <div class="content">
                    <br>
                    <p>We're here to assist you!</p>
                    <p>In light of the current COVID-19 situation, the Philippine Normal University Office of Student Affairs and Student Services (OSASS) has launched the PNU CRISIS HELPLINE to help PNU students, faculty members, administrative staff, and frontliners reach free, confidential telephone crisis lines, information, and referral services. The PNU Crisis Helpline will be operating in a flexible working arrangement as we strive to provide continuing support and care for the mental and emotional well-being of the PNU Community and our frontliners in these times of crisis.</p>
                    <p>This program hopes to respond to the arising needs and concerns of our stakeholders. This is staffed by licensed counselors and trained volunteers from a network of crisis call centers located across Metro Manila and nearby provinces. It provides: (a) crisis intervention for people in emotional distress related to COVID-19; (b) information on how to recognize distress and its effects on individuals and families; (c) assistance related to medical, economic and academic concerns; and (d) referrals to trained responders in handling crises for additional follow-up care and support.</p>
                    <p>If you need assistance, leave us a message on our Facebook Page on how we can assist you.</p>
